=== EXAMPLE: scdoc_Overviews_Operators_ex47 ===

DESCRIPTION: A dark pure_tone sound, with square_like oscillator character around 1002 Hz, featuring punchy attack and sustained envelope, filtered with resonant_steep_rolloff character, and spectrally simple.

CATEGORIES:
  attack_time: punchy
  brightness: dark
  crest_factor_db: sustained
  envelope_flatness: flat
  harmonic_to_noise_ratio: pure_tone
  spectral_complexity_mean: simple
  spectral_flux_normalized: stable
  spectral_slope: steep_rolloff
  temporal_centroid: balanced

SYNTHESIS CONCEPTS (key values):
[oscillator]
  fundamental_freq: 1002.1316
  harmonic_decay_rate: -7.7304
  harmonic_regularity: 0.9530
  pitch_clarity: 235.3394
  inharmonicity: 0.2940
  type: square_like
[filter]
  spectral_slope: -4.7330
  resonance_freq: 990.5273

SUPERCOLLIDER CODE:
// Title: Operators Example 47
// Author: SC Documentation
// URL: http://doc.sccode.org/Overviews/Operators.html
// Tags: Operators, Overviews
// ---
// --- Example 47 ---
{ FSinOsc.ar(500).scaleneg(Line.ar(1,-1,4)) }.play;
